The paper deals with motion planning, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). It also involves the use of path-planning algorithms, which are often based on machine learning and optimization techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also discusses manipulation planning for a robot arm, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes experiments on scenarios in $\mathbb{R}^{2}$ and $\mathbb{R}^{4}$, which suggests the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for visualization and analysis.
